18// Helper functions for extracting fields from encoded instructions.
19// InsnType must either be integral or an APInt-like object that must:
20// * Have a static const max_size_in_bits equal to the number of bits in the
21// encoding.
22// * be default-constructible and copy-constructible
23// * be constructible from a uint64_t
24// * be constructible from an APInt (this can be private)
25// * Support getBitsSet(loBit, hiBit)
26// * be convertible to uint64_t
27// * Support the ~, &, ==, !=, and |= operators with other objects of the same type
28// * Support shift (<<, >>) with signed and unsigned integers on the RHS
29// * Support put (<<) to raw_ostream&
30template <typename InsnType>
31#if defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__)
32__declspec(noinline)
33#endif
34static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
35 unsigned numBits, std::true_type) {
36 assert(startBit + numBits <= 64 && "Cannot support >64-bit extractions!");
37 assert(startBit + numBits <= (sizeof(InsnType) * 8) &&
38 "Instruction field out of bounds!");
39 InsnType fieldMask;
40 if (numBits == sizeof(InsnType) * 8)
41 fieldMask = (InsnType)(-1LL);
42 else
43 fieldMask = (((InsnType)1 << numBits) - 1) << startBit;
44 return (insn & fieldMask) >> startBit;
45}
46
47template <typename InsnType>
48static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
49 unsigned numBits, std::false_type) {
50 assert(startBit + numBits <= InsnType::max_size_in_bits && "Instruction field out of bounds!");
51 InsnType fieldMask = InsnType::getBitsSet(0, numBits);
52 return (insn >> startBit) & fieldMask;
53}
54
55template <typename InsnType>
56static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
57 unsigned numBits) {
58 return fieldFromInstruction(insn, startBit, numBits, std::is_integral<InsnType>());
59}

1756static bool checkDecoderPredicate(unsigned Idx, const FeatureBitset &Bits) {
1757 switch (Idx) {
1758 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid index!");
1759 case 0:
1760 return (Bits[Sparc::FeatureV9]);
1761 case 1:
1762 return (Bits[Sparc::FeaturePWRPSR]);
1763 case 2:
1764 return (Bits[Sparc::FeatureVIS3]);
1765 case 3:
1766 return (Bits[Sparc::FeatureVIS]);
1767 case 4:
1768 return (Bits[Sparc::FeatureVIS2]);
1769 }
1770}

2336 if (DecodeIntRegsRegisterClass(MI, tmp, Address, Decoder) == MCDisassembler::Fail) { return MCDisassembler::Fail; }
2337 tmp = fieldFromInstruction(insn, 5, 8);
2338 MI.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(tmp));
2339 return S;
2340 case 86:
2341 tmp = fieldFromInstruction(insn, 25, 5);
2342 if (DecodeI64RegsRegisterClass(MI, tmp, Address, Decoder) == MCDisassembler::Fail) { return MCDisassembler::Fail; }
2343 tmp = fieldFromInstruction(insn, 14, 5);
2344 if (DecodeI64RegsRegisterClass(MI, tmp, Address, Decoder) == MCDisassembler::Fail) { return MCDisassembler::Fail; }
2345 tmp = fieldFromInstruction(insn, 0, 5);
2346 if (DecodeI64RegsRegisterClass(MI, tmp, Address, Decoder) == MCDisassembler::Fail) { return MCDisassembler::Fail; }
2347 tmp = fieldFromInstruction(insn, 25, 5);
2348 if (DecodeI64RegsRegisterClass(MI, tmp, Address, Decoder) == MCDisassembler::Fail) { return MCDisassembler::Fail; }
2349 return S;
2350 case 87:
2351 if (DecodeTRAP(MI, insn, Address, Decoder) == MCDisassembler::Fail) { return MCDisassembler::Fail; }
2352 return S;
2353 }
2354}
2355
2356template <typename InsnType>
2357static DecodeStatus decodeInstruction(const uint8_t DecodeTable[], MCInst &MI,
2358 InsnType insn, uint64_t Address,
2359 const void *DisAsm,
2360 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI) {
2361 const FeatureBitset &Bits = STI.getFeatureBits();
2362
2363 const uint8_t *Ptr = DecodeTable;
2364 InsnType CurFieldValue = 0;
2365 DecodeStatus S = MCDisassembler::Success;
2366 while (true) {
2367 ptrdiff_t Loc = Ptr - DecodeTable;
2368 switch (*Ptr) {
2369 default:
2370 errs() << Loc << ": Unexpected decode table opcode!\n";
2371 return MCDisassembler::Fail;
2372 case MCD::OPC_ExtractField: {
2373 unsigned Start = *++Ptr;
2374 unsigned Len = *++Ptr;
2375 ++Ptr;
2376 CurFieldValue = fieldFromInstruction(insn, Start, Len);
2377 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_ExtractField(" << Start << ", "
2378 << Len << "): " << CurFieldValue << "\n");
2379 break;
2380 }
2381 case MCD::OPC_FilterValue: {
2382 // Decode the field value.
2383 unsigned Len;
2384 InsnType Val = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
2385 Ptr += Len;
2386 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
2387 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
2388 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
2389 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
2390
2391 // Perform the filter operation.
2392 if (Val != CurFieldValue)
2393 Ptr += NumToSkip;
2394 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_FilterValue(" << Val << ", " << NumToSkip
2395 << "): " << ((Val != CurFieldValue) ? "FAIL:" : "PASS:")
2396 << " continuing at " << (Ptr - DecodeTable) << "\n");
2397
2398 break;
2399 }
2400 case MCD::OPC_CheckField: {
2401 unsigned Start = *++Ptr;
2402 unsigned Len = *++Ptr;
2403 InsnType FieldValue = fieldFromInstruction(insn, Start, Len);
2404 // Decode the field value.
2405 InsnType ExpectedValue = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
2406 Ptr += Len;
2407 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
2408 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
2409 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
2410 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
2411
2412 // If the actual and expected values don't match, skip.
2413 if (ExpectedValue != FieldValue)
2414 Ptr += NumToSkip;
2415 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_CheckField(" << Start << ", "
2416 << Len << ", " << ExpectedValue << ", " << NumToSkip
2417 << "): FieldValue = " << FieldValue << ", ExpectedValue = "
2418 << ExpectedValue << ": "
2419 << ((ExpectedValue == FieldValue) ? "PASS\n" : "FAIL\n"));
2420 break;
2421 }
2422 case MCD::OPC_CheckPredicate: {
2423 unsigned Len;
2424 // Decode the Predicate Index value.
2425 unsigned PIdx = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
2426 Ptr += Len;
2427 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
2428 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
2429 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
2430 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
2431 // Check the predicate.
2432 bool Pred;
2433 if (!(Pred = checkDecoderPredicate(PIdx, Bits)))
2434 Ptr += NumToSkip;
2435 (void)Pred;
2436 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_CheckPredicate(" << PIdx << "): "
2437 << (Pred ? "PASS\n" : "FAIL\n"));
2438
2439 break;
2440 }
2441 case MCD::OPC_Decode: {
2442 unsigned Len;
2443 // Decode the Opcode value.
2444 unsigned Opc = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
2445 Ptr += Len;
2446 unsigned DecodeIdx = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
2447 Ptr += Len;
2448
2449 MI.clear();
2450 MI.setOpcode(Opc);
2451 bool DecodeComplete;
2452 S = decodeToMCInst(S, DecodeIdx, insn, MI, Address, DisAsm, DecodeComplete);
2453 assert(DecodeComplete);
2454
2455 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_Decode: opcode " << Opc
2456 << ", using decoder " << DecodeIdx << ": "
2457 << (S != MCDisassembler::Fail ? "PASS" : "FAIL") << "\n");
2458 return S;
2459 }
2460 case MCD::OPC_TryDecode: {
2461 unsigned Len;
2462 // Decode the Opcode value.
2463 unsigned Opc = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
2464 Ptr += Len;
2465 unsigned DecodeIdx = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
2466 Ptr += Len;
2467 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
2468 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
2469 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
2470 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
2471
2472 // Perform the decode operation.
2473 MCInst TmpMI;
2474 TmpMI.setOpcode(Opc);
2475 bool DecodeComplete;
2476 S = decodeToMCInst(S, DecodeIdx, insn, TmpMI, Address, DisAsm, DecodeComplete);
2477 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_TryDecode: opcode " << Opc
2478 << ", using decoder " << DecodeIdx << ": ");
2479
2480 if (DecodeComplete) {
2481 // Decoding complete.
2482 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (S != MCDisassembler::Fail ? "PASS" : "FAIL") << "\n");
2483 MI = TmpMI;
2484 return S;
2485 } else {
2486 assert(S == MCDisassembler::Fail);
2487 // If the decoding was incomplete, skip.
2488 Ptr += NumToSkip;
2489 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FAIL: continuing at " << (Ptr - DecodeTable) << "\n");
2490 // Reset decode status. This also drops a SoftFail status that could be
2491 // set before the decode attempt.
2492 S = MCDisassembler::Success;
2493 }
2494 break;
2495 }
2496 case MCD::OPC_SoftFail: {
2497 // Decode the mask values.
2498 unsigned Len;
2499 InsnType PositiveMask = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
2500 Ptr += Len;
2501 InsnType NegativeMask = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
2502 Ptr += Len;
2503 bool Fail = (insn & PositiveMask) || (~insn & NegativeMask);
2504 if (Fail)
2505 S = MCDisassembler::SoftFail;
2506 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_SoftFail: " << (Fail ? "FAIL\n" : "PASS\n"));
2507 break;
2508 }
2509 case MCD::OPC_Fail: {
2510 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_Fail\n");
2511 return MCDisassembler::Fail;
2512 }
2513 }
2514 }
2515 llvm_unreachable("bogosity detected in disassembler state machine!");
2516}
